toxcast.description: This dataset offers predictions related to the potential toxicological effects of molecules on various cellular and genetic targets. Each entry represents a distinct biological or cellular response.

SR-ATAD5.description: ATAD5 protein, related to DNA damage response.

tox21.description: This dataset revolves around predicting the toxicity of molecules against various nuclear receptors and stress response pathways. The different outputs such as 'NR-AR', 'NR-AhR', etc., represent different biological targets and pathways, and the goal is to predict how molecules will interact with or affect them.

high.description: Predicts high metabolic stability of a molecule.

low.description: Predicts low metabolic stability of a molecule.

metstab.description: This dataset gives insights into the metabolic stability of molecules. High metabolic stability often results in a longer half-life, influencing drug dosage and frequency.

Class.description: Predicts whether a given molecule will inhibit the enzyme beta-secretase 1 (BACE1), which is important in Alzheimer's disease pathology.

bace.description: A dataset focused on predicting the inhibitory effects of molecules on the enzyme beta-secretase 1 (BACE1). BACE1 inhibition is a potential target for Alzheimer's disease treatment.

Hepatobiliary disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with disorders of the liver, gallbladder, or bile ducts.

Metabolism and nutrition disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is related to metabolic or nutritional disturbances.

Product issues.description: Predicts if there are any issues with the molecule as a product.

Eye disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is linked with eye-related disorders.

Investigations.description: Predicts if a molecule requires further investigations.

Musculoskeletal and connective tissue di.description: Predicts if a molecule affects the muscles, bones, or connective tissues.

Gastrointestinal disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with disorders of the digestive system.

Social circumstances.description: Predicts if a molecule has effects influenced by social factors.

Immune system disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule impacts the immune system.

Reproductive system and breast disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule affects reproductive organs or breasts.

Neoplasms benign, malignant and unspecif.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with tumors, whether benign, malignant or unspecified.

General disorders and administration sit.description: Predicts general disorders or issues at the administration site caused by a molecule.

Endocrine disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with hormone-related disorders.

Surgical and medical procedures.description: Predicts if a molecule is related to complications in surgical or medical procedures.

Vascular disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule affects the vascular system.

Blood and lymphatic system disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is related to disorders of the blood or lymphatic system.

Skin and subcutaneous tissue disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule causes disorders of the skin or underlying tissue.

Congenital, familial and genetic disorde.description: Predicts if a molecule is linked to hereditary or birth-related disorders.

Infections and infestations.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with increased risk of infections or infestations.

Respiratory, thoracic and mediastinal di.description: Predicts if a molecule impacts the respiratory system or surrounding regions.

Psychiatric disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule causes or exacerbates mental health disorders.

Renal and urinary disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule affects the kidneys or urinary system.

Pregnancy, puerperium and perinatal cond.description: Predicts if a molecule is associated with conditions related to pregnancy or the period immediately after childbirth.

Ear and labyrinth disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule is linked to disorders of the ear or inner ear.

Cardiac disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule affects the heart.

Nervous system disorders.description: Predicts if a molecule impacts the nervous system.

Injury, poisoning and procedural complic.description: Predicts if a molecule is related to injuries, poisonings, or complications from procedures.

sider.description: A dataset highlighting the potential side effects of molecules. Each field represents a category of adverse effects. This dataset aids in understanding the safety profile and potential side effects associated with molecules.
